#ubntu







 Step-by-Step Guide
Step 1: Open Terminal
Press Ctrl + Alt + T to open the terminal on your Ubuntu system.

Step 2: Create a Directory (Optional)
You can create a folder to organize your project:

bash
Copy
Edit
mkdir dashboard_project
cd dashboard_project
Step 3: Create and Open the HTML File Using gedit
Run the following command to open the text editor:

bash
Copy
Edit
gedit index.html
This will open gedit, the default GUI text editor in Ubuntu, with a new file named index.html.

Step 4: Paste Your HTML Code
In the gedit window that opens, paste your entire HTML code (including the <!DOCTYPE html> line).

Save the file: Ctrl + S

Close gedit: Ctrl + Q or click the close button.

Step 5: Open HTML File in Browser
Back in the terminal, type:

bash
Copy
Edit
xdg-open index.html
This command opens the HTML file in your default web browser (e.g., Firefox or Chrome).







      
